    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <bold>IADLXDisplayGammaChangedListener</bold> interface is implemented in the application to receive an event from ADLX when the display gamma changes.</para>
<para><table rows="4" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>InterfaceId:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Smart Pointer Interface Name:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherits:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherited By:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para>An instance of the implemented <bold>IADLXDisplayGammaChangedListener</bold> interface must be passed to <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_display_changed_handling__add_display_gamma_event_listener" kindref="compound">AddDisplayGammaEventListener</ref> to register for notifications when the display gamma changes.<linebreak/>
 For more information about subscribing for event notifications, refer to <ref refid="page_guide_event" kindref="compound">Subscribing to Event Notifications using ADLX</ref>.<linebreak/>
</para>
<para><heading level="2">Methods </heading>
</para>
<para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Method   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_display_gamma_changed_listener__on_display_gamma_changed" kindref="compound">OnDisplayGammaChanged</ref>   </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>The <bold>OnDisplayGammaChanged</bold> method is called by ADLX when the display gamma changes.   </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
